label: Sastre has an account on this site, and logging in makes some small improvements to what you can see. This website's layout is easily navigable, so it's good to check for a general overview. However, it's not 100% reliable, especially for historical information
notes: Wiki Source. Sastre has an account on this site, and logging in makes some small improvements to what you can see. This website's layout is easily navigable, so it's good to check for a general overview. However, it's not 100% reliable, especially for historical information (including establishment date), so any information to be cited in a report should ideally be verified at https://www.unternehmensregister.de (see below). Moreover, companyhouse.de tries to charge extra for certain information, such as shareholder details, which can be obtained for free from unternehmensregister.de. Never buy any filings from companyhouse.de, because the same documents can all be obtained for free from unternehmensregister.de.

resources.name: Sastre has an account on this site, and logging in

label: by individuals' names
notes: Wiki Source. by individuals' names (at least if you're logged in with Sastre's account). Individuals' pages on companyhouse.de should list all past and current affiliations as a director ("Geschäftsführer") or "Prokurist" ("authorized signatory"), as well as their date of birth and (most recent) place of residence. Ownership relationships aren't usually listed (though occasionally they are, especially for KG companies). The date of birth listed on companyhouse.de is reliable, but the dates of affiliations are very unreliable, so affiliations should ideally be confirmed on unternehmensregister.de as outlined above, if you're going to mention them in a report. There's no simple way to search for companies that a person owns; the best approach is to use Unternehmensregister.de to check the ownership of any companies where the subject is a director, or where you have other reason to suspect a connection.

label: and https://www.unternehmensregister.de. In terms of the statements' contents, both websites are equally reliable, though if for a given company one website doesn't have them, check the other.

label: '''Cadastre'''] provides real estate records, which can be searched by address only
notes: Wiki Source. '''Cadastre'''] provides real estate records, which can be searched by address only (not owner name). Search the target address through the search box, and open the parcel file, which gives basic identification and background details - note that area is measured in hectares (ha), ares (a = 100 m2), and centiares (ca = 1 m2). Detailed local parcel maps from different dates (if available) are listed beneath the background data and accessible in low resolution; full resolution maps can be ordered for free by opening the low resolution map and clicking the link at the bottom of the pop-up box.

notes: Wiki Source. Rejestr.io]. Its main advantage is that it can be searched by an individual's name. Without a subscription, you can search an individual's name and see all their current affiliations. With a subscription, you can see their historical affiliations too. With a subscription, you can also download a company's annual financial reports (these should also be available from an official database, probably for free, so try to find that rather than buying a subscription just to get annual reports, and update the wiki if you find it). The subscription isn't too expensive and can be cancelled any time, so it can be worth paying for a month just for a single project (just remember to cancel before the month ends). You can also get a 14-day free trial, though you'll need to use a card that's never been used for this before.

label: Pierce offshore structures via regulatory filings (MEKH, BaFin, SEC)
notes: Regulators (MEKH for energy, BaFin for finance, SEC for listed) require disclosure that reveals offshore beneficial ownership. Check if entity operates in regulated sector.
examples: Hungarian MEKH reveals Swiss/Cyprus energy company ownership
German BaFin reveals Jersey/BVI financial holdings
US SEC reveals Marshall Islands/Cayman listed company shareholders

resources.note: Auto-added: Generic arbitrage search

label: Find person data via their foreign company filings
notes: When individuals file as beneficial owners or directors in LU/GB/CY/NL, they must disclose passport numbers, addresses, and connections not available in their home jurisdiction.
examples: Luxembourg filings reveal German passport numbers and addresses
UK Companies House reveals Jersey/BVI resident directors' UK activities
Cyprus registry reveals Russian businessmen's directorship history

resources.note: Auto-added: Generic arbitrage search

label: Reveal offshore subsidiary via transparent parent jurisdiction
notes: Dutch B.V./N.V., Luxembourg S.à r.l., UK Ltd, German GmbH must disclose subsidiary structures in annual reports, revealing BVI/Cyprus/Cayman subsidiaries.
examples: Dutch holding reveals BVI subsidiary ownership chain
Luxembourg S.à r.l. annual report shows Cyprus intermediary structure
UK parent company accounts disclose offshore subsidiary valuations

resources.note: Auto-added: Generic arbitrage search

label: Reveal offshore parent via local subsidiary filings
notes: When offshore structures have operating subsidiaries in transparent jurisdictions (UK, DE, FR, NL), those subsidiaries must file accounts showing their parent ownership chain.
examples: UK subsidiary Companies House filing reveals BVI parent structure
German subsidiary reveals Swiss AG ultimate parent
French subsidiary KBIS filing shows Luxembourg holding parent

resources.note: Auto-added: Generic arbitrage search

label: Access via bilateral treaties or EU directives
notes: EU AMLD beneficial ownership registers, EU-wide transparency directives, bilateral tax treaties may provide access to information not otherwise available.
examples: EU beneficial ownership registers reveal previously hidden UBOs
Tax treaty information exchange reveals undisclosed holdings

resources.note: Auto-added: Generic arbitrage search

label: US SEC filings for foreign/offshore entities with US nexus
notes: Foreign entities listed on US exchanges or with significant US shareholders must file with SEC (Form 20-F, Schedule 13D/G), revealing ownership not disclosed in home jurisdiction.
examples: Cayman fund files Form 13F revealing portfolio holdings
Marshall Islands shipping company 20-F reveals beneficial owners
Bermuda insurer SEC filings show shareholder structure

label: UK Companies House reveals offshore residents' UK activities
notes: Offshore residents who are directors of UK companies appear in Companies House with their declared address, DOB, and full directorship history across all UK entities.
examples: Jersey resident's UK company directorships reveal business network
Dubai resident's UK property company shows UK address history
Singapore resident's UK holding company reveals group structure

notes: WHOIS registrant email, abuse contact, admin contact. Website scraping for mailto: links, contact pages, footer emails. Privacy protection may redact WHOIS emails.

notes: Entity extraction and normalization. Converts company_beneficial_owner_name to person_name entity. Enables chaining UBO data to person investigation flows.

notes: Via Majestic, Ahrefs, SEMrush APIs, or Common Crawl link graph analysis. Returns backlink URLs and referring domains. Critical for domain clustering and network mapping.

notes: Crawl domain homepage and key pages, extract all external links. Common Crawl provides historical outlink data. Used for network mapping and entity connection discovery.

label: Find breach records for person name
notes: Search breach databases by name (less reliable than email search due to common names). DeHashed, IntelX support name-based queries. Best when combined with location/DOB for disambiguation.

label: Direct breach lookup by email
notes: DeHashed, HIBP (Have I Been Pwned), IntelX, BreachDirectory, Snusbase. Returns breach_password_hash, breach_source, breach_date. K-anonymity methods used for HIBP to protect privacy.

notes: Extracts outgoing links from domain homepage and key pages. Uses CommonCrawl for historical outlink data.

label: Company lookup from ATLAS unified index (3.2M records)
notes: Unified company corpus from WDC Schema.org (9.6M), Affiliate LinkedIn (2.8M), ET3 Reports. Deduped by tax_id → domain → name+country.

label: Person lookup from ATLAS unified index (6.4M records)
notes: Unified person corpus from WDC Schema.org (6.8M), breach records, ET3 Reports. Deduped by linkedin → email → name+employer.

label: LinkedIn profile lookup from ATLAS unified index (2.9M records)
notes: Unified LinkedIn corpus from Affiliate (2.8M companies), WDC sameAs links, ET3 Reports. Both person and company profiles.

label: Email lookup from ATLAS unified index (breach + communication patterns)
notes: Unified email corpus from Kazaword (92K), breach records (197K), WDC. Includes breach exposure and communication patterns.

label: Phone lookup from ATLAS unified index (49K records)
notes: Unified phone corpus from WDC person/org entities, breach records. E.164 normalized with country code detection.

label: Find all persons associated with a company (via ATLAS unified indices)
notes: Cross-references companies_unified → persons_unified via employer_domains and embedded_edges.

label: Find all companies associated with a person (via ATLAS unified indices)
notes: Cross-references persons_unified → companies_unified via employer names and domains.

label: Advanced company search with location/industry/size filters (3.2M records)
notes: Filtered company search. Supports: country, municipality (city), region, industry, naics, founding_year, employee_count. Auto-creates location nodes.

label: List companies in a country (ATLAS)
notes: Browse companies by country. Returns top companies with industry distribution.

label: List companies in an industry (ATLAS)
notes: Browse companies by industry. Returns companies with geographic distribution.

label: Check email in breach databases (250M+ records)
notes: Search breach records by email. Returns breach name, year, password hash type, and hints.

output_schema.breach_name: string - Name of the breach (LinkedIn, Adobe, etc.)
output_schema.hash_type: string - Type of password hash (sha1, bcrypt, 3des, etc.)
output_schema.password_hint: string - Password hint if available (Adobe breach)

label: Find all breached emails from a domain
notes: Search breach records by email domain. Returns all exposed emails from that domain.

label: Get statistics for a specific breach
notes: Get statistics about a specific breach - top domains, email patterns, etc.

label: UK PSC (Persons with Significant Control) lookup
notes: Search UK PSC register for beneficial owners. Returns individual PSCs (with partial DOB) and corporate PSCs (with foreign jurisdiction info).

output_schema.psc_records: array - All PSCs for the company
output_schema.foreign_companies: array - Corporate PSCs with their jurisdiction (for cross-country routing)

label: Find UK companies where person is PSC
notes: Search UK PSC register by person name to find companies they control.

label: OpenOwnership beneficial ownership lookup
notes: Search OpenOwnership BODS data for beneficial ownership. Covers multiple jurisdictions.

label: Extract foreign company jurisdictions from PSC data
notes: Extracts foreign company jurisdictions from corporate PSC entries. Routes foreign companies to their respective country registries.

resources.note: Parses corporate PSC data and routes to country-specific indices

output_schema.foreign_company_jurisdiction: string - ISO 2-letter country code (DE, FR, BVI, etc.)
output_schema.foreign_company_reg_number: string - Registration number in foreign jurisdiction
output_schema.psc_foreign_companies_list: array - All foreign companies with their jurisdictions for batch routing

label: UK PSC per-country index (foreign corporate PSCs)
notes: Index of corporate PSCs in UK companies, grouped by foreign jurisdiction. Use for: "Find all German companies that are PSCs of UK companies".

label: UK properties by owner company jurisdiction
notes: Find UK properties owned by companies from a specific jurisdiction. E.g., "All UK property owned by BVI companies".

output_schema.property_owner_jurisdiction: string - ISO country code of owner
output_schema.property_owner_company_reg: string - Registration number in owner jurisdiction

label: Fetch full profile of foreign corporate PSC via Torpedo
notes: Uses Torpedo to fetch full company profile from foreign registry based on PSC jurisdiction. Dynamic jurisdiction routing.

resources.note: Torpedo routes to best source for the jurisdiction extracted from PSC data

label: UK FCA regulated firm lookup by company name
notes: Search FCA Register for regulated firms. Returns authorisation status, permissions, individuals, disciplinary history and fines.

output_schema.fca_status: string - Authorised, Registered, No longer authorised, etc.
output_schema.fca_individuals: array - Authorised individuals at the firm
output_schema.fca_fines: array - Fines imposed with amounts and dates

label: UK FCA firm lookup by FRN (Firm Reference Number)
notes: Direct FCA firm lookup by FRN. Returns full regulatory profile.

label: UK FCA authorised individual lookup
notes: Search FCA Register for authorised individuals. Returns their IRN, controlled functions, and firm history.

output_schema.fca_individual_controlled_functions: array - CF roles (CF1 Director, CF10 Compliance, etc.)
output_schema.fca_individual_firm_history: array - Firms where individual was/is authorised

label: UK FCA disciplinary actions and fines search
notes: Search FCA disciplinary history for firms and individuals. Returns fines, bans, restrictions.

resources.note: Fallback: search FCA website for final notices

label: UK FCA permissions and licence verification
notes: Detailed permissions, requirements, waivers and exclusions for an FCA firm.

label: UK Land Registry CCOD - UK Company Property Holdings
notes: Search CCOD (Commercial and Corporate Ownership Dataset) for UK-registered companies owning property. Contains ~3.5M titles.

label: UK Land Registry OCOD - Overseas Company Property Holdings
notes: Search OCOD (Overseas Company Ownership Dataset) for foreign companies owning UK property. Contains ~100K titles.

label: UK Land Registry Leases - Leasehold Properties
notes: Search UK Land Registry leasehold dataset. Contains ~7.67M lease records with terms, dates, and alienation clauses.

label: UK Property Network Analysis - Cross-reference CCOD/OCOD/Leases
notes: Cross-reference company across CCOD, OCOD, and Leases datasets to build property portfolio network.

label: UK Companies House - Company Profile
notes: Fetch full company profile from Companies House API including status, type, registered office, SIC codes.

label: UK Companies House - Company Officers
notes: Fetch officers (directors, secretaries) for a UK company from Companies House.

label: UK Companies House - Filing History
notes: Fetch filing history (annual returns, accounts, resolutions) from Companies House.

label: UK Companies House - Charges Register
notes: Fetch charges (mortgages, debentures, fixed/floating charges) from Companies House.

label: UK Companies House - Insolvency History
notes: Fetch insolvency history (administration, liquidation, receivership) from Companies House.

label: Company to domain via CYMONIDES domain profiles
description: Search 5.8M domain profiles with company_name field to find company websites.
notes: CYMONIDES unified_domain_profiles index. Maps company names to domains/websites.

label: Company LinkedIn profiles via CYMONIDES
description: Search 2.8M LinkedIn company pages with name, industry, employee counts.
notes: CYMONIDES affiliate_linkedin_companies index. 2.8M LinkedIn company profiles.

label: Company registry data via CYMONIDES

notes: CYMONIDES companies_unified index. Aggregated from OpenCorporates, Companies House, etc.

label: Local business lookup via WDC
description: Search 478K local business entities with addresses and phone numbers.
notes: Web Data Commons LocalBusiness entities. Schema.org structured data.

label: Beneficial ownership via OpenOwnership
description: Search 21M+ beneficial ownership statements from Open Ownership Register.
notes: CYMONIDES openownership index. Beneficial owners and control statements.

label: Domain metrics from Common Crawl graph
description: Get domain-level metrics from 100M+ Common Crawl domain vertices.
notes: CYMONIDES cymonides_cc_domain_vertices. Page counts, inlink/outlink counts.

label: Domain backlinks from Common Crawl graph

notes: CYMONIDES cymonides_cc_domain_edges. Backlinks and anchor text profiles.

label: Breach lookup via CYMONIDES
description: Search 119M+ breach records for email, username, password, hash.
notes: CYMONIDES breach_records index. Consolidated breach data.

label: Full-text document search via CYMONIDES
description: Search 13M+ documents (PDFs, web pages, reports) in main corpus.
notes: CYMONIDES cymonides-2 index. Main document corpus with full-text search.
